        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Diallo is a good signing. I had hoped that Arsenal would sign him last season. Left-footed CBs who are good defensively AND on the ball are extremely rare. Dortmund now have the option to play a back 3 without any big holes in the CB/LB channels likely to appear. He needs work but he has raw ability. Selling Sokratis made sense for both clubs involved but they have replaced him with a major long-term prospect imo. It is also good for both Dortmund and the player himself that Pulisic seems to be staying. Favre is known as a refiner of rough diamonds and the player will develop far better while in an arena where he can make a few mistakes rather than the goldfish-bowl atmosphere which you get with big teams playing in big cities like Madrid. Hopefully Julian Weigl stays and gets back to full fitness soon to form a midfield trio with Delaney and Witsel. They should provide a nutritious bed in which the front three of Pulisic, Philipp and Reus can flourish.
